Package: meteoTidy
Title: Quality Control, Correction, and Archiving of Meteorological Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Robin", "Shannon", , "32329438+vorpalvorpal@users.noreply.github.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Maurits", "Evers", role = "ctb")
  )
Description: Ingests meteorological observations and forecasts from multiple
    sources, applies quality control, gap-filling, and bias correction, and
    archives the results as a canonical, versioned Parquet store. Unlike
    general-purpose API clients such as 'weatherOz', 'meteoTidy' does not
    itself implement provider transports for every source; it wraps
    'weatherOz' for 'SILO' access and layers curation, calibration, and a
    tidy read API on top of raw observations and forecasts from several
    providers.
